<table width="100%" border=0><tr><td valign=top>
    <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 bgcolor=ffffff width=100%><tr><td>
    <table border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=1 bgcolor=000000 width=100%><tr><td>
    <table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 bgcolor=cfcfbb width=100%><tr><td align=left>
    <font size=3 color="#363636"><b>Lied to again.... surprise, surprise, surprise.....</b></font><br>
    <font size=2>
    Posted on Thursday, February 22 @ 07:58:02 EST by <a href="http://www.noows.com">zamtil</a><font size=2>Contributed by: <a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Furor_Planedefiler">Furor_Planedefiler</a></font></td></tr></table></td></tr></table><br><a href="search.php?query=&topic=31"><img src=images/topics/editorial.gif border=0 Alt="Rants & Reviews" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>Ever feel like they're after you? After this patch which should have been nicknamed after my guild on the patch server message, I sure as hell do.... Almost every and I mean EVERY nerf had something to do with the way we've been playing this game for the past 2 years. <br><br><br><br>I also got a great laugh out of my tash sticks... I know that was directed right at me.... good job guys. It only took 2+ years to fix Tash and after all the dead enchanters bitching about how much hate it built up, a warrior got it fixed. Way to listen to your customer base.<br><br>

But I digress....<br><br>

About a month ago I had a conversation with a few certain people at Verant Interactive about the upcoming nerfs (now realized nerfs). In this conversation we discussed the impact such nerfs might have on gameplay. The general concensus was, then, that if nerfs like this would be turned live, SEVERAL encounters would require tuning DOWN. I was essentially promised that SEVERAL of those encounters would be tuned down when the mass nerf patch did go live. Fast forward to today... Not ONE, and I mean NOT ONE, uber mob was tuned down in the least. As a matter of fact, Yelinak's difficulty was dramatically increased (something that was TOTALLY unnessecary to begin with).<br><br>

Add to this the fact that I can no longer do my job as a warrior (Taunt and Tank) and an incredibly, INCREDIBLY stupid move on cleric healing aggro (I am pretty sure when we discussed this, we didn't want the clerics to instantly die from uber encounters, right guys?) and you have one broken game. <br><br>

Game Designing 101 - When designing a game, you look at each class and put that class in a 'perfect world' situation. As a designer you say to yourself, "What is this class' job and how are they going to get it done?" Please explain to me HOW THE FUCK I am supposed to tank anything over level 57? I found it incredibly amusing in Temple of Veeshan tonight when I ran around like a total fucking dumbshit hitting level 60+ mobs in the back as they are tearing a new asshole on my clerics. Here I am, thinking, a level 60 warrior with easily the best gear attainable by anyone is beating on this level 60+ mob with all his force and this mob is chasing around every cleric and druid and shaman that dared cast a heal spell on some unfortunate tank victim (most likely a hybrid). The logistics of the game are totally fubared.... 
<br><br>
Lastly, to the designer that created the Dain Dumbfuckreaver IV encounter. Let me clue you in to something, YOU CANNOT KILL DAIN THE WAY HE WAS INTENDED BY YOUR DIVINE FUCKING MAJESTY. Let me again put up that perfect world scenario for you, mm, k? Let's assume one did not try to take him in the well and decided to fight him IN his throne room. What would you need? Again, in that perfect world setting we discussed earlier, you would need a magician of level 55+ in each group, and to clear out his chamber. So let's assume we do this... ok done! Fast huh? Now we are ready for the charge! Excited yet? We're gonna take on the Dain as he was designed to be!  Ok guys, GO! So the assault on this incredibly retarded and defective mob begins. We're all beating on Dain, he's down a good 1% health when all of a sudden I get a flashback from 'Top Gun.' "Where'd he go? WHERE'D WHO GOOOOOO?" Brilliant move on your side buddy... If that stupid shit is gonna Touch players into the pit, then he better GOD DAMNED forget them once he does it... otherwise the son-of-a bitch runs out his chamber down through the ENTIRE castle and out to the zoneline to try and reach the guy he's really pissed off at (probably your cleric or some stupid ranger). DO YOU EVEN PLAY THIS GAME? Now you've added MORE spots where the Dain will *POOF* if you try and pull him... again, let me clue you in to something. People like to use their brains when devising strategies to kill shit. Instead of rewarding players that do this you penalize them by adding MORE places the Dain can poof! Good JOB MAN!!!
<br><br>
Part one of my rant is done... if you are gonna flame, let me give you a pre-emptive 'go fuck yourself' comment... ok proceed...
</td></tr></table><br></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign=top width=200>
