<br>
Now the problem is that the damage output of the high end encounters is totally off scale. Verant scaled the hate already partially due to increased CH efficiency with added tank hitpoints (the 800hate to 2000hate jump), but never did anything to compensate the HUGE jump that happens around lvl 60 when you swap from grinding dual 200 hitters to killing QUAD 600 hitting ubermobs. So the CH efficiency change by like 3 times between pro-51 to post-51 requires the hate increase to be multiplied by 2.5, but damage output increasing by a factor of 6 doesn't warrant any kind of change. Oh sorry not 6 since the 200 hitters can be slowed to about 25% of their normal damage output... the actual factor is 24. Verant people might not be terribly good at math, but they should be able to notice that, um, the hate becomes a slight problem in these cases, since CH has to be more or less chain cast at the tanks.<br>
<br>
Now Verant has a few choices.<br>
a) Let things go back to the way they were, which really does make a clerics job ridiculously easy in grinding ~55<br>
b) Tune down the ubermobs to require less healing. Obviously the problem with this is that they might become rather trivial, which isn't a problem with solution a.<br>
c) Fix around with hate so that the hate increase works differently for ubermobs.. ie effectively have them work hate like they used to while keeping the healing hate increase for other fights.<br>
d) Tune down ubermob damage output and figure out something creative to make them non-trivial. No this doesn't mean a million hps. No this does DEFINITELY not mean you have to have the fuggin thing poof in a million spots on the route it likes to take. But you could have stuff that likes to summon new mobs that hit for 150 or so or anything creative... This would be preferred solution, but I guess it depends on if you have the actual creativity. (don't get stuck on the single example, was made up in about 10sec, those that work at Verant should probably work more than 10sec per day)<br>
